fnos-fan
========

This repository bundles third-party source code:

  kmod/qnap8528/ — the qnap8528 Linux kernel module
    Copyright (c) 0xGiddi and contributors
    Source:  https://github.com/0xGiddi/qnap8528
    License: GPL-2.0-or-later  (SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-or-later)
    fnOS-specific fork: https://github.com/gzxiexl/qnap8528

    Vendored unmodified for offline / reproducible image builds. All copyright
    and the GPL-2.0-or-later license terms of the original authors apply to
    every file under kmod/qnap8528/. See the SPDX headers in the source.

  kmod/it87/ — the it87 Linux Super-I/O hardware-monitoring driver
    Copyright (c) Chris Gauthron, Jean Delvare, Frank Crawford and contributors (lm-sensors)
    Source:  https://github.com/frankcrawford/it87
    License: GPL-2.0-or-later  (SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-or-later)

    Out-of-tree fork adding support for newer ITE Super-I/O chips (e.g. IT8613E)
    not yet covered by the in-tree it87. Vendored for offline / reproducible
    image builds (only the upstream Research/ datasheet archive is omitted; the
    module source is intact); built and loaded only on non-QNAP x86 boards that
    expose no pwm otherwise. All copyright and the GPL-2.0-or-later license terms
    of the original authors apply to every file under kmod/it87/. See the SPDX
    headers in the source.

